The functional equation \(f(x^2 - y^2) = x f(x) - y f(y)\) holds for all real \(x, y\). Setting \(x = y\) gives \(f(0) = x f(x) - x f(x) = 0\), so \(z = f(0) = 0\). Thus, the number of regions created by the light pulse path is \(z + 2021 = 2021\).

The light pulse path in the square corresponds to a billiard path from one corner to another. Using the unfolding method, the path is described by coprime positive integers \(p\) and \(q\), where the slope is \(q/p\). The number of bounces \(n\) is \(p + q - 2\), and the number of regions \(R\) is given by \(R = \frac{(p+1)(q+1)}{2}\). Setting \(R = 2021\) yields \((p+1)(q+1) = 4042\). Factoring \(4042 = 2 \times 43 \times 47\) gives possible factor pairs for \((p+1, q+1)\): \((2, 2021)\), \((43, 94)\), and \((47, 86)\). The condition \(\gcd(p, q) = 1\) (i.e., \(\gcd(p+1 - 1, q+1 - 1) = 1\)) eliminates \((43, 94)\) since \(\gcd(42, 93) = 3\). The pair \((47, 86)\) gives \(\gcd(46, 85) = 1\), and \((2, 2021)\) gives \(\gcd(1, 2020) = 1\). The corresponding \(n\) values are \(n = (47 + 86) - 4 = 129\) and \(n = (2 + 2021) - 4 = 2019\). The smallest is \(n = 129\).

